values:
(Since Dean got a birthday post/letter in 2012 I thought the Mr. deserved one too. )

HAPPY BIRTHDAY JACK! I'm not even mad that its 10:30 and we are already home from celebrating. It makes me laugh when I think of how excited we were for a mid week date night and how, these days, "mid week date night" requires about a week of planning in advance and negotiating with our babysitter just how late she can stay out on school night.  I know I've been mocking you about this for weeks but I am DYING over the fact that you are 30 years old! How did that happen?! Imagine you could go back to the kid you were when we first met and tell him everything we would go through together in your 20's. Do you think you'd ever believe it? Or better yet, would you still ask me out that night?!  I love you more than I could ever put into a paragraph. Honestly my instinct was to make this lighthearted and funny (seriously, you are SO old!) but now that I'm sitting here with a little bit of quiet for the first time all day all I can think about is how loved I hope you feel and how I hope you know just how lucky I think I am to be your wife. You are re-tucking our children into bed right now and I could never do justice in words to the feeling I get when I see you with them. I am so grateful for every one of your 30 years and am so excited to start another decade of your life with you.  <3

Happy Birthday Dean! I'm sorry that it has been 3 years since I honored you with your very own birthday post, good thing you know how much I love you even with out it. And in case you need reminding, I do! I love you like crazy! You and I know just how complicated all that love has made things the last few years but here I am, still telling the world that you are one of the greatest men I will ever know. Thank you for being my friend for over a decade! For loving me when I haven't been very lovable, for being right next to me for some of the best and worst moments of my life and making me laugh each step of the way. I should also send some love to your mama, who raised you right and treats me like one of her own. (Thank you!) I am about to burst with excitement waiting for that baby of yours to be born. Me and mine would not be the same with out you so I just know that you are going to be one amazing dad. I hope this year treats you well!
Avery has a baby brother, Grayson Jack. I promise to come back one day and tell you all about him.

I'm taking a quick break from the festivities for another LJ tradition- Jackson's birthday post! My HUSBAND (it still makes me laugh to say that!) is 27 years old today! I would be pissed if I had to share my birthday with all the Gator hoopla but I don't think Jackson minds one bit. He is having a great day. 26 was a way better year than 25 was for sure but I have to say that I think 27 will the best yet. <3  

(Love that man, happy he was born, think he's getting old etc,etc... Haha. )
This is my annual "Happy Birthday Dean!" post. He is 24 today! I could not ask for a better friend. :)
I have a lot I want to say but the most important is that I put our wedding invitations in the mail today. SCARY! EXCITING! Haha.

Helllo!  

I know that I have been MIA for a really long time and I promise a huge update one of these days but FIRST I wanted to let you all know about something that all of a sudden is really important to me. 

Getting listed on the bone marrow donor registry was one of the first things I put on my new 101 in 1001 goal list. In order to cover the cost of the tissue-typing kit getting registered usually costs about 50 dollars BUT if you decide to join between now and September 22nd it will cost you nothing! The NASCAR Foundation is sponsoring a huge bone marrow donor drive. I know that most of us are not about to get to a track anytime soon so I wanted to show you how you can participate virtually. All you need to do is follow the link I will provide and fill out the required information on the National Marrow Donor Program website. It should take no more than 10-15 minutes to get through the health history questions and contact information.  They will send you a kit, you swab your cheek a couple of times and send it back with the hope that one day you will match someone in need. 

Keep in mind that registering to be a donor is a real commitment. I have seen one of the ways they get to that all important bone marrow and trust me, it did not look like fun! Despite that, I realize how important it is to donate what I can and how, in the grand scheme of things, how little a few days with sore hips will inconvenience my life. If you do decide to sign up PLEASE understand what you are saying you are willing to do. For someone to be told that there is a potential match out in the world only to find out you aren't actually willing to go through with the donation process would be devastating. 

The link below not only will let you start registering free of charge but will give you all the information you need on the registry itself and the process of actually being a bone marrow donor. Feel free to ask me any questions and I will do my best to answer with what I know. 

http://www.marrow.org/HELP/Join_the_Donor_Registry/Join_Now_Sponsored/join_now_sponsored.html



Make sure you follow that link, or find the NASCAR Foundation link on bottom right side of the homepage (www.marrow.org) to receive the promotion code. The code that was used when I registered was "NASC262101" so if you still can't get the code to automatically pop up try that. :) On the last page it will have a spot for credit card information but if your total cost is $0 you do NOT need to enter that info, it will let you advance without it. Keep clicking "next" or whatever it says until you get to the final page which will give you your NMDP ID.  

If this is not your thing that is ok, I totally get it, but please pass along the information to someone you think would be willing to join. The NMDP could really use mixed race donors and young men are generally the ideal choice but ANYONE who gets put on the registry could potentially be called upon to donate. We hope that Jackson will never need a bone marrow transplant but if he does it is a stranger who volunteers to be on this list that will be the most important part of saving his life.  Pass it on!

I think 2007 is going to be for friend's only.

(New ones always welcome!)

Avery fell asleep early. I just sat down with a bottle of beer and an ice cream sandwich. Jackson and I are doing laundry. He's on the phone. He's arguing with someone. Lots of "intense face." I like seeing him without him seeing me see him. It's like watching him sleep when he's really sleeping. When I was away with Avery over Thanksgiving I missed that. I've gotten used to sleeping next to him every night. I need to stop questioning my happiness. :) I don't know. I'm in a weird mood. Maybe it's the combination of sugar and alcohol.

I took Avery to the mall today and waited in line to have her picture taken with Santa. She didn't mind me handing her over to a fat, hairy old guy. I can't believe I handed her over to a fat, hairy old guy. 

Less than a week until Christmas. It was 80 degrees outside today.

Suri Cruise has about 17 times as much hair as Avery (Cruz). Avery thinks she got cheated. I told her that while she didn't get a full head of pony tail worthy hair from birth, she lucked out and got parents who are not as batshit insane as Miss Suri's. (Even if she may sometimes think we are.)

The ladies on my friends list are still alive and in generally good physical and mental health.

confirm / deny
I'm listening to The London Philharmonic do Beethoven.  I want to walk down the aisle to Romance No.1 (in G! for the violin and orchestra! as if I know what that means!)

last thing tonight, I promise. I'm going to bed and sleeping off my total irritation at today. Yahoo! is at it again and will explain it better than I can: People have been pushing your buttons a lot lately, and even if it hasn't been bugging you too much, you may start feeling frustrated. You're more sensitive now, and you could easily let some silly stuff get to you if you're not careful. To prepare for this eventual annoyance, keep your priorities straight. Avoid any dramas, and you may need to let go of something you've been working for to keep your composure. Think of the big picture, no matter what you do.

Daily Extended Forecast for May 20, 2006

You're not weak if you ask for help. Before things get to the panic phase, seek the assistance that you know you need. Friends who have been there before are waiting for you to ask -- they have some wise advice you need to hear. Ask for what you need today. No bad assumptions will be made -- your reputation is stronger than you think! Emotionally, you are on solid ground, so be as affectionate as you want. Expressing your feelings will make you feel good!

Gather up the precious things in your life and hold on tight! No one is threatening you, but conditions could arise if you're not fully aware of the value of what you have. Friends, family and a romantic partner add so much to your life -- realize that nothing should be taken for granted. Career-wise, you would do well to prepare a backup plan or alternative goal. Don't be shy about reminding the higher ups that you have more to offer than they are utilizing.

I HAVE A DAUGHTER!
Avery Cruz finally decided she had enough of my uterus May 4th at 12:03 AM. She weighed 7 pounds, 6 ounces and was 20 inches long (& beautiful, of course.) Details and all that to come later I promise. We just got home a couple hours ago, family/friends are still here offering help and "advice" and we're all still just getting used to each other :) We've been ordered to be back at the hospital tomorrow afternoon for a check on her jaundice but beyond that everything is great. I feel good, still exhausted and in shock that she's MINE and I get to (have to? lol) keep her, but good! :)

Life always involves a balancing act between how things are and how you'd like them to be. On the one hand, you have to recognize reality for what it is. On the other hand, you have to be able to visualize ways it could be better. The thing to avoid is imagining reality as something that it isn't. You won't fall into the trap of wishful believing as long as you're vigilant.

I'm behind on my journal but I'm a little behind here at school as well. The days have been flying by much too fast for me lately. This weekend was filled with learning about what the next few weeks have in store for me, what labor may be like, what my body is going to do after it gives birth and then what I have to do with it when this thing I have been cooking for 9 months makes it out into the real world. It's pretty overwhelming! I'll be back as soon as I get all caught up in my "real" life :)

It's Sunday which means I'm 29 weeks pregnant exactly today- which usually warrants one of those annoying pregnacy updates. If you hate them then tonight you lucked out because I'm too busy to read my email really good and make obnoxious comments about it. (Not too busy to tell you I'm too busy though!) I'll probably do it tomorrow. I just wanted to mention that I had a really great birthday and a great birthday weekend. More detailed updates to follow, I'm sure. Grey's Anatomy was also soo good again tonight. It definitely didn't disappoint. Now I'm going to get back to cleaning my teeth and my face and then slapping body butter on any body part that's growing. Then it's homework time. I took a post dinner nap to night in preparation.

Dean felt the baby kicking for the first time last night. There was non-stop flipping feelings going on and I felt like I could feel some kicks from the outside but couldn't tell if it was just because I knew where they were coming from on the inside. Dean put his hand on my stomach and right away pulled it back in surprise. It's such a crazy feeling. He got a couple more kicks and then no more even though s/he was still going nuts on the inside. While his desire to keep touching me now is pretty annoying, his enthusiasm is kind of cute.

You'll be wearing your emotions like a t-shirt today -- so they'll be the very first thing others see when they first see you. Fortunately, the heavens have arranged for you to be in a wonderful mood -- right along with your sweetheart. No matter how unpredictable and unusual your moods are, then, they'll at least be pleasant. So don't worry about offending anyone, and don't hold anything back. The fans will love you, as is. And so will your lucky companion. spending the day with Jackson :)

MERRY CHRISTMAS!!!




<small>(I probably wont get around to all the fun that is 22 weeks, look for it on Monday!)</small>

"Knowing you, you're looking to the future in advance of everyone else, weighing your choices and reevaluating your plans. It's definitely big-picture stuff, but it's exactly the kind of thing you're best at. Right now, though, your view is curiously limited -- it could be your emotions are getting in the way, or the daily routine has you worn down. Activate your imagination -- there's a choice here you're not seeing, and it may be the right one. " What the heck Yahoo! What are you talking about? What is that supposed to mean? What am I not seeing? Horoscopes should just tell you what to do instead of just acting all cosmically intelligent and then leaving you hanging. It's not nice. (Is the Universe still driving? When is it going to be safe to come out?)

Tomorrow I'll be home and while I'm not sure how I feel about that really, I am so antsy that I want to just get out of here and go. Now. I'm also not sure whether I'm about to scream or start crying. But one of those I think. Neither will make the best friend glad to have me around. And it's not that I want to leave because I've been having a bad time. Not at all. I'm just being HORMONAL and I'm sick of myself. Courtney asked me what was (is) wrong and I told her I am sick of being stuck in my own skin. She looked at me like I had 9 heads and told me to get over it. Thanks a lot. She doesn't let me mope. I feel seriously sleep deprived. Which would be fine if, you know, I actually wasn't getting enough sleep. But thats one thing that is not lacking in my life right now. I feel like punching someone. Starting with Jackson, for just existing. Seriously. I WANT to start an argument with him over anything just so I can yell at him about everything. Lucky him. I don't know why but I'm having "I don't like you very much" feelings about him. Just thinking about his face makes me more annoyed with myself because I know I am being an irrational girl when I think homicidal thoughts about him. (Actually, they are far from homicidal, mostly I just want to give him the silent treatment and kick him or something. I'm tough. Don't piss me off.) I'm not really this miserable, I'm just having a moment.

You're about to shock your family and/or your parents, and amaze anyone else who's never seen this side of you before. Sure, you're usually detached and eerily objective -- and you're good at it, too. But now? Well, right about now, you'll be hard-pressed to keep the tears from your eyes at a good baby food commercial. Don't panic, this, too, shall pass.

You may feel a bit of an internal struggle taking place inside you now. That doesn't mean it's going to be unpleasant, only that what you're thinking may be at odds with what you're feeling -- or with what you feel it's necessary to do right now. There's only one thing to do: Let go and let the universe do the driving. Your instinct is second to none, and you'll know when it's safe to come out.

When I left for school last year, Deans mom gave me the book Oh, the Places You'll Go! by Dr. Seuss. It is such a smart book and so, in honor of the few of you who I know are heading off to bigger and better places next week , I thought I would be cheesy for a second and pass along the inspiration. ( & for anyone else who just needs some wise Dr. Seuss words right now. oh and ps, its long and I'm not cutting it so stop crying.) Congratulations! Today is your day. You're off to Great Places! You're off and away! You have brains in your head. You have feet in your shoes You can steer yourself any direction you choose. You're on your own. And you know what you know. And YOU are the guy who'll decide where to go. You'll look up and down streets. Look 'em over with care. About some you will say, "I don't choose to go there." With your head full of brains and your shoes full of feet, you're too smart to go down any not-so-good street. And you may not find any you'll want to go down. In that case, of course, you'll head straight out of town. It's opener there in the wide open air. Out there things can happen and frequently do to people as brainy and footsy as you. And when things start to happen, don't worry. Don't stew. Just go right along. You'll start happening too. OH! THE PLACES YOU'LL GO! You won't lag behind, because you'll have the speed. You'll pass the whole gang and you'll soon take the lead. Wherever you fly, you'll be the best of the best. Wherever you go, you will top all the rest. Except when you don't Because, sometimes, you won't. I'm sorry to say so but, sadly, it's true that Bang-ups and Hang-ups can happen to you. You can get all hung up in a prickle-ly perch. And your gang will fly on. You'll be left in a Lurch. You'll come down from the Lurch with an unpleasant bump. And the chances are, then, that you'll be in a Slump. And when you're in a Slump, you're not in for much fun. Un-slumping yourself is not easily done. You will come to a place where the streets are not marked. Some windows are lighted. But mostly they're darked. A place you could sprain both your elbow and chin! Do you dare to stay out? Do you dare to go in? How much can you lose? How much can you win? And IF you go in, should you turn left or right... or right-and-three-quarters? Or, maybe, not quite? Or go around back and sneak in from behind? Simple it's not, I'm afraid you will find, for a mind-maker-upper to make up his mind. You can get so confused that you'll start in to race down long wiggled roads at a break-necking pace and grind on for miles across weirdish wild space, headed, I fear, toward a most useless place. The Waiting Place... ...for people just waiting. Waiting for a train to go or a bus to come, or a plane to go or the mail to come, or the rain to go or the phone to ring, or the snow to snow or waiting around for a Yes or No or waiting for their hair to grow. Everyone is just waiting. Waiting for the fish to bite or waiting for wind to fly a kite or waiting around for Friday night or waiting, perhaps, for their Uncle Jake or a pot to boil, or a Better Break or a string of pearls, or a pair of pants or a wig with curls, or Another Chance. Everyone is just waiting. NO! That's not for you! Somehow you'll escape all that waiting and staying. You'll find the bright places where Boom Bands are playing. With banner flip-flapping, once more you'll ride high! Ready for anything under the sky. Ready because you're that kind of a guy! Oh, the places you'll go! There is fun to be done! There are points to be scored. there are games to be won. And the magical things you can do with that ball will make you the winning-est winner of all. Fame! You'll be famous as famous can be, with the whole wide world watching you win on TV. I'm afraid that some times you'll play lonely games too. Games you can't win 'cause you'll play against you. All Alone! Whether you like it or not, Alone will be something you'll be quite a lot. And when you're alone, there's a very good chance you'll meet things that scare you right out of your pants. There are some, down the road between hither and yon, that can scare you so much you won't want to go on. But on you will go though the weather be foul On you will go though your enemies prowl On you will go though the Hakken-Kraks howl Onward up many a frightening creek, though your arms may get sore and your sneakers may leak. On and on you will hike and I know you'll hike far and face up to your problems whatever they are. You'll get mixed up, of course, as you already know. You'll get mixed up with many strange birds as you go. So be sure when you step. Step with care and great tact and remember that Life's a Great Balancing Act. Just never forget to be dexterous and deft. And never mix up your right foot with your left. And will you succeed? Yes! You will, indeed! (98 and 3/4 percent guaranteed.) KID, YOU'LL MOVE MOUNTAINS! So... be your name Buxbaum or Bixby or Bray or Mordecai Ali Van Allen O'Shea, you're off to Great Places! Today is your day! Your mountain is waiting. So... get on your way! (the end. from her to me and from me to you, "Enjoy the journey..." ) Good luck!

I think, of all the things I did this summer, what I will remember the most (happily) were the big trips my brother and I took to the beach. We would wake up really early and drive across the state, get breakfast and then get in the water before anyone else did. If we didnt see anyone there first, he would tell me, "We were the first ones to touch the ocean today!" There's something really exciting about being the first people to stick your toes in the Atlantic that day, even if it is only that one small spot of the ocean you got to before anyone else. It was like our secret. We'd run around, take pictures, nap, eat lunch, practice surfing and then come home. He'd usually sleep in the car on the way home. My mom let him let his hair grow this summer and all the sun and salt left it really blonde and crazy. He would hate it if he knew I saw, but he cried when he had to go get it cut. Mostly because hes going to miss the hair, I know, but I'd like to think part of it was because he's going to miss me a little bit too. Hopefully he wont be too embarassed when he sees that I framed a picture of him dead asleep in the sand, drooling on a surfboard.
Why was it harder when I went away to school than it was when he left for school?
